<div id="review_416057699" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/416057699" />
    <a title="Lexie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3754297-lexie"><img alt="Lexie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1334616400p2/3754297.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/416057699?book_show_action=true">Sep 16, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lexie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lexie" href="/user/show/3754297-lexie">Lexie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3754297-lexie?shelf=read-in-2012">read-in-2012</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer416057699" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13097703154302888848">I literally read this book in one day. Yeah, it is that good!<br/><br/>The Guy Next Door was a pleasant surprise. What I figured would be a light romance was in fact a deeply emotional story about love, loss, and family. It was centered around a sweet love story but it also had plenty of drama and suspense (my favorite combination!)<br/><br/>I love how strong and capable Eva turns out to be. With all the pain and emotional upheaval in her life, it is amazing that she continues with faith and optimism. She steps up </span>
  <span id="freeText13097703154302888848" style="display:none">I literally read this book in one day. Yeah, it is that good!<br /><br />The Guy Next Door was a pleasant surprise. What I figured would be a light romance was in fact a deeply emotional story about love, loss, and family. It was centered around a sweet love story but it also had plenty of drama and suspense (my favorite combination!)<br /><br />I love how strong and capable Eva turns out to be. With all the pain and emotional upheaval in her life, it is amazing that she continues with faith and optimism. She steps up to whatever comes her way and makes some tough decisions, even knowing how much pain they will cause her.<br /><br />I also enjoyed Eva's relationship with Peter (the "guy next door"). I liked how slowly and easily they transitioned from friends to something more. It was comfortable and sweet and was a great example of building a relationship based upon friendship.<br /><br />And though Eva's "obsession" with Sean drives me crazy, I totally understand where she was coming from. I have known many guys like that in my life and seen girls close to me fall for them. Even though he was very manipulative, he did have some redeeming qualities that made him somewhat irresistable.<br /><br />Overall, I can't say enough good things about this book and would definitely recommend scheduling a day to read it - you won't want to put it down!</span>
  <a data-text-id="13097703154302888848" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


