<div id="review_407351424" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/407351424" />
    <a title="Ranee Clark" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2387872-ranee-clark"><img alt="Ranee Clark" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1534623435p2/2387872.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/407351424?book_show_action=true">Sep 04, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ranee Clark" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ranee Clark" href="/user/show/2387872-ranee-clark">Ranee Clark</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer407351424" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer80128502317564898">Audience: Adult<br/>The Rating: **** (Really liked it)<br/>The Good: THE GUY NEXT DOOR has a really great mix of romance and thrill with a generous dosing of real-life. I loved that it wasn&apos;t just your run-of-the-mill boy-meets-girl with some adventure and twists and turns thrown in. Eva has to deal with tragic circumstances (curse you Kate for making me cry!). I became very involved in the story, sharing in Eva&apos;s frustrations, triumphs, and especially the things she learns.<br/>The Bad: I guessed a few things</span>
  <span id="freeText80128502317564898" style="display:none">Audience: Adult<br />The Rating: **** (Really liked it)<br />The Good: THE GUY NEXT DOOR has a really great mix of romance and thrill with a generous dosing of real-life. I loved that it wasn't just your run-of-the-mill boy-meets-girl with some adventure and twists and turns thrown in. Eva has to deal with tragic circumstances (curse you Kate for making me cry!). I became very involved in the story, sharing in Eva's frustrations, triumphs, and especially the things she learns.<br />The Bad: I guessed a few things about Peter well before Eva suspected anything, which made me wonder why Eva wasn't seeing what I saw. But, in all honesty, it didn't bother me that much.<br />The Recommendation: I've heard many people saying lately that LDS romance has moved way beyond fluff literature and this book exemplifies that statement. It's a great read if you love romance, and as I mentioned above, it's got a good dose of depth and thrill too.<br />Disclaimer: Clean, LDS Romance, Mildly intense moments.<br /><br />See full review at <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://raneesclark.blogspot.com/2012/10/review-guy-next-door-by-kate-palmer.html">http://raneesclark.blogspot.com/2012/...</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="80128502317564898" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
