<span id="freeTextContainer17218477350274228608">I was thinking (from the cover) that this would be a suspenseful book. While parts of it were, especially in the second half, it was more of a romance, with a love triangle. <br/><br/>Eva has lost both parents and finds herself engaged to a man who seems very controlling. When her only sister and brother-in-law pass away and she is left to raise her newborn niece, her fiance gives her an ultimatum. While she is trying to figure out her new life, she becomes close to her neighbor, Peter. <br/><br/>I felt the emotion</span>
  <span id="freeText17218477350274228608" style="display:none">I was thinking (from the cover) that this would be a suspenseful book. While parts of it were, especially in the second half, it was more of a romance, with a love triangle. <br /><br />Eva has lost both parents and finds herself engaged to a man who seems very controlling. When her only sister and brother-in-law pass away and she is left to raise her newborn niece, her fiance gives her an ultimatum. While she is trying to figure out her new life, she becomes close to her neighbor, Peter. <br /><br />I felt the emotion that Eva experienced--her loneliness, misery, joy in discovering herself, confusion, etc. I enjoyed the second half a bit more than the first part. <br /><br />Content: clean--LDS fiction; no memorable language, but some peril and a dangerous situation.</span>
