<div id="review_583733091" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/583733091" />
    <a title="Charlynn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/801101-charlynn"><img alt="Charlynn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1200719002p2/801101.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/583733091?book_show_action=true">Apr 07, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Charlynn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Charlynn" href="/user/show/801101-charlynn">Charlynn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer583733091" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11727185447852619352">I finally got around to reading this and I&apos;m so glad I did! Mostly romance with a dash of suspense, and the characters and situations are interesting without seeming contrived. There was one part that even made me cry, which usually bugs me but this time I didn&apos;t feel emotionally manipulated. The character is LDS and there are some spiritual moments but the author pulled those off without it being cheesy and/or preachy. A few twists in the plot kept me reading and I finished in a day and a half.</span>
  <span id="freeText11727185447852619352" style="display:none">I finally got around to reading this and I'm so glad I did! Mostly romance with a dash of suspense, and the characters and situations are interesting without seeming contrived. There was one part that even made me cry, which usually bugs me but this time I didn't feel emotionally manipulated. The character is LDS and there are some spiritual moments but the author pulled those off without it being cheesy and/or preachy. A few twists in the plot kept me reading and I finished in a day and a half. Good stuff!</span>
